a:10:{i:0;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:3:"100";s:3:"url";s:3:"n/A";s:9:"publisher";s:3:"IGN";s:6:"author";s:3:"n/A";s:6:"review";s:128:"Matt Reeves’ violent, thrilling, darkly beautiful take on The Batman more than justifies its place in the franchise’s canon.";}i:1;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"90";s:3:"url";s:113:"https://www.slashfilm.com/780391/the-batman-review-the-dark-knight-returns-in-what-may-be-the-best-bat-movie-yet/";s:9:"publisher";s:9:"Slashfilm";s:6:"author";s:17:"Chris Evangelista";s:6:"review";s:141:"Do we really need yet another "Batman" reboot? The answer, after watching Matt Reeves' tremendous The Batman, is apparently a resounding yes.";}i:2;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"88";s:3:"url";s:71:"https://www.thewrap.com/the-batman-review-robert-pattinson-zoe-kravitz/";s:9:"publisher";s:7:"TheWrap";s:6:"author";s:14:"Todd Gilchrist";s:6:"review";s:179:"With Pattinson glowering beneath his cowl, Reeves creates a Batman whose psychology is at least as interesting as his crime-fighting activities, for the first time in a long time.";}i:3;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"83";s:3:"url";s:67:"https://consequence.net/2022/02/the-batman-review-robert-pattinson/";s:9:"publisher";s:11:"Consequence";s:6:"author";s:18:"Liz Shannon Miller";s:6:"review";s:239:"What this film does achieve is telling a solid new Batman story, one with some pretty compelling twists and a strong point-of-view on who, exactly, the Caped Crusader is. By default, that makes it one of the better Batman movies ever made.";}i:4;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"80";s:3:"url";s:3:"n/A";s:9:"publisher";s:11:"Screen Rant";s:6:"author";s:13:"Mae Abdulbaki";s:6:"review";s:148:"With exhilarating action scenes, a layered story & poignant, in-depth characterization, The Batman is a worthy addition to the live-action DC slate.";}i:5;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"75";s:3:"url";s:82:"https://rogersmovienation.com/2022/02/28/movie-review-a-batman-for-a-vengeful-era/";s:9:"publisher";s:12:"Movie Nation";s:6:"author";s:11:"Roger Moore";s:6:"review";s:451:"It’s too long, and maybe there’s a little too much concern about the way Pattinson’s hair flops over one eye. But from first frame to last, Reeves matches the master, Christopher Nolan in two important regards. As in the last Nolan “Dark Knight,” this Batman is embattled and almost overwhelmed by a city and its institutions coming apart at the seams. And like Nolan’s “Knights,” this beast of a movie looks, sounds and plays as epic.";}i:6;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"75";s:3:"url";s:3:"n/A";s:9:"publisher";s:14:"Slant Magazine";s:6:"author";s:9:"Jake Cole";s:6:"review";s:139:"The film stands apart for thoughtfully suggesting that Batman might actually one day make Gotham a better place, and not merely a safer one";}i:7;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"75";s:3:"url";s:68:"https://www.indiewire.com/2022/02/the-batman-review-2022-1234702878/";s:9:"publisher";s:9:"IndieWire";s:6:"author";s:13:"David Ehrlich";s:6:"review";s:77:"By far the most nuanced relationship here is that between Batman and Riddler.";}i:8;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"70";s:3:"url";s:69:"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/22951429/the-batman-movie-review-2022";s:9:"publisher";s:7:"Polygon";s:6:"author";s:13:"Joshua Rivera";s:6:"review";s:82:"There is nothing particularly bold about The Batman. Its strength is in execution.";}i:9;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"60";s:3:"url";s:115:"https://www.azcentral.com/story/entertainment/movies/billgoodykoontz/2022/02/28/the-batman-movie-review/6964688001/";s:9:"publisher";s:16:"Arizona Republic";s:6:"author";s:16:"Bill Goodykoontz";s:6:"review";s:274:"The Batman is impressively made. The acting is first rate, and the chemistry between Pattinson and Kravitz is magnetic. It’s meant to be an important statement. It’s just not a lot of, you know, fun. Or as someone famously put it in another Batman movie, Why so serious?";}}